12 SECTION 16. ORS 430.644 is amended to read:
13 430.644. Within the limits of available funds, community mental health programs shall provide
14 those services as defined in ORS 430.630 (3)(a) to (h) to persons in the following order of priority:
15 (1) Those persons who, in accordance with the assessment of professionals in the field of mental
16 health, are at immediate risk of hospitalization for the treatment of mental [or emotional disturb-
17 ances] health disorders or are in need of continuing services to avoid hospitalization or pose a
18 hazard to the health and safety of themselves, including the potential for suicide, or others and those
19 persons under 18 years of age who, in accordance with the assessment of professionals in the field
20 of mental health, are at immediate risk of removal from their homes for treatment of mental [or
21 emotional disturbances] health conditions or exhibit behavior indicating high risk of developing
22 [disturbances] conditions of a severe or persistent nature;
23 (2) Those persons who, because of the nature of their mental illness, their geographic location
24 or their family income, are least capable of obtaining assistance from the private sector; and
25 (3) Those persons who, in accordance with the assessment of professionals in the field of mental
26 health, are experiencing mental [or emotional disturbances] health disorders but will not require
27 hospitalization in the foreseeable future.
