9 SECTION 21. ORS 430.380 is amended to read:
10 430.380. (1) There is established in the General Fund of the State Treasury an account to be
11 known as the Mental Health [Alcoholism and Drug Services] and Substance Use Account. Moneys
12 deposited in the account are continuously appropriated for the purposes of ORS 430.345 to 430.380
13 and to provide funding for sobering facilities registered under ORS 430.262. Moneys deposited in the
14 account may be invested in the manner prescribed in ORS 293.701 to 293.857.
