16 Substance Use Account shall be continuously appropriated to the counties on the basis of popu-
17 lation. The counties must use the moneys for the establishment, operation and maintenance of al-
18 cohol and drug abuse prevention, early intervention and treatment services and for local matching
19 funds under ORS 430.345 to 430.380. The counties may use up to 10 percent of the moneys appro-
20 priated under this subsection to provide funds for sobering facilities registered under ORS 430.262.
21 (3) Forty percent of the moneys shall be continuously appropriated to the Oregon Health Au-
22 thority to be used for state matching funds to counties for alcohol and drug abuse prevention, early
23 intervention and treatment services pursuant to ORS 430.345 to 430.380. The authority may use up
24 to 10 percent of the moneys appropriated under this subsection for matching funds to counties for
25 sobering facilities registered under ORS 430.262.
26 (4) Twenty percent of the moneys shall be continuously appropriated to the Oregon Health Au-
27 thority to be used for alcohol and drug abuse prevention, early intervention and treatment services
28 for adults in custody of correctional and penal institutions and for parolees therefrom and for
29 probationers as provided pursuant to rules of the authority. However, prior to expenditure of mon-
30 eys under this subsection, the authority must present its program plans for approval to the appro-
31 priate legislative body which is either the Joint Ways and Means Committee during a session of the
32 Legislative Assembly or the Emergency Board during the interim between sessions.
